Last year I spent about a day trying to make a completely insulated Gmail account, just on general principles, that was only going to be accessed through a virtual machine and a proxy, with credentials stored offline, and from there use that same virtual machine and proxy for social media accounts that would allow me to look at things here and there online that otherwise don't let you see anything in their "walled gardens."

I wanted to try this as proof of concept, and because OPSEC and privacy are important to me just on general principles. It turns out I couldn't. So I won't be doing any of the rest of that.
